      "kind": "constraint",
      "summary": "I found the issue. The RTM parser's regex patterns for task IDs don't recognize the \"-DEF\" suffix. Looking at `plan_visualizer.py` line 130: ```python task_match = re.match(r'^\\*\\*([A-Z]+(?:-[A-Z0-9]+)*-[\\d-]+(?:-ALT)?)(?:\\*\\*:|:\\*\\*)\\s+(.+)', line) ``` The pattern only recognizes \"-ALT\" as a valid suffix, not \"-DEF\". Let me fix this by updating the regex patterns to also recognize \"-DEF\" suffix.",
      "details": "I found the issue. The RTM parser's regex patterns for task IDs don't recognize the \"-DEF\" suffix. Looking at `plan_visualizer.py` line 130: ```python task_match = re.match(r'^\\*\\*([A-Z]+(?:-[A-Z0-9]+)*-[\\d-]+(?:-ALT)?)(?:\\*\\*:|:\\*\\*)\\s+(.+)', line) ``` The pattern only recognizes \"-ALT\" as a valid suffix, not \"-DEF\". Let me fix this by updating the regex patterns to also recognize \"-DEF\" suffix.",
